AGI - An earthquake of magnitude 7.7 > hit the northwest of Myanmar. > The earthquake caused serious damage in several cities of the country and at least 144 deaths and over 700 wounded, according to health sources in a very first budget. The devastating earthquake was felt in nearby Thailand, where several buildings were damaged and at least one, a skyscraper, collapsed in Bangkok.&nbsp;&nbsp;
The earthquake was the second largest city in Myanmar, Mandalay.> The damage is "enormous" and the number of victims is "in the order, at least, of the hundreds", said a local health source quoted by the Bbc. The Red Cross also states that there were "significant damages". &nbsp;
The earthquake was recorded at a depth of 10 kilometers, around 12:50 local time (6:20 GMT), according to the most detailed surveys of the US Geological Service (USGS). The Italian institute, Ingv, also found the shock.&nbsp;
In Myanmar the military junta in power has decreed the state of emergency in six regions > and has launched a rare demand for international humanitarian aid. The head of the military junta, Min Aung Hlaing, arrived in one of the main hospitals of Naypyidaw where the wounded are treated, even on the street.
The earthquake was strongly felt throughout Thailand > north and central, and then in the south, even in the capital Bangkok, where residents ran on the street while buildings trembled.&nbsp; Thai Prime Minister Paetongtarn Shinawatra declared the state of emergency for the capital Bangkok.&nbsp;
<div </div
According to the Beijing earthquake agency, shocks were also felt in the south-western province of Yunnan. According to the Xinhua press agency, China Earthquake Networks Center> (CENC) stated that the shock was of magnitude 7-9. In a social post, CENC said that "the shocks were warned in Yunnan". &nbsp;
<h2> Naypyidaw hospital declared "mass victims zones"</h2>
The main hospital in the capital of Myanmar has become a "mass victims zone". Files of wounded were cured outside the general hospital's emergency room by 1,000 beds, some were twisted by pain, others were lying still while relatives were trying to comfort them. In the main hospital the wounded are cured in the street, with intravenous phlebs hanging at the bars. The streets close to the National Museum of Naypyidaw were deformed and broken because of the shocks, as reported by two Afp journalists who were in the building at the time of the shock.&nbsp;
<div </div
<h2>Edifici evacuati a Bangkok</h2>
Another earthquake hit, on the magnitude of 5.5 - was recorded in Bangkok. Residents of the Thai capital are on the road, preying to fear, while the buildings trembled. All offices and shops were evacuated by the authorities. &nbsp;
"I heard it and I was sleeping in the house, I ran as quickly as possible in pajamas outside the building", said Duangjai, a resident of the popular tourist town of Chiang Mai, after the shocks were felt throughout northern, central and then south Thailand.
<h2>81 persons trapped in a building under construction which collapsed
A 30-storey building skyscraper for government offices collapsed in Bangkok and three people died. Deputy Prime Minister Phumtham Wechayachai said there are 81 people trapped under the rubble and that at least three people died.
The building in the north of the Thai capital was reduced to a tangle of rubble and metal twisted in seconds.
<div </div
Urgent meeting in Thailand
<
After the strong shocks that struck the country, Thai premier Paetongtarn Shinawatra was forced to stop an official visit to the southern island of Phuket to hold an "empty meeting". It is learned from a post on X of the Thai authorities, after evacuating buildings and shops in the capital, Bangkok.&nbsp;
</div
